Let's think step by step. This problem can be solved using the difference-of-squares factoring technique. By definition, $a^2-b^2=(a+b)(ab)$, so $$\begin{aligned}
513^2-487^2&amp;= (513+487)(513-487)
\end{aligned}$$ We simplify both terms inside the parentheses to get $(1000)(26)=26000.$ The answer is: 26000.
